════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A quiet river bend with prestige appeal.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Tennyson sits on a tight bend in the Brisbane River, anchored by the Queensland Tennis Centre and the Tennyson Reach apartment development on the former power station site. It is one of Brisbane's smallest suburbs by population, which keeps turnover low and the prestige river-frontage segment tightly held. The suburb attracts established buyers from across the inner south and the western corridor who want privacy, river access and direct connection to the South West Bikeway, without leaving the inner-Brisbane school catchments behind.
    </p>
