<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know Tennyson well. I understand the buyer profile, the value of a true riverside position, and how to run a campaign that reaches the small, highly specific buyer pool that drives this prestige market.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Tennyson is genuinely two markets stitched together by the river. The riverside houses, mostly large family blocks along King Arthur Terrace and the adjoining streets, form the prestige segment, with values driven by frontage, outlook and the depth of the block back from the water. Tennyson Reach contributes the contemporary apartment stock, with its own buyer pool of downsizers, professionals and investors who want lock-and-leave living with river outlook and Tennis Centre proximity. The Queensland Tennis Centre itself anchors the lifestyle profile of the suburb, and the Brisbane Olympic 2032 planning has only sharpened buyer interest in the precinct. Sellers here benefit from precision in positioning more than from broad reach.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229;">
